{"id":205,"date":"2017-07-03T15:06:36","date_gmt":"2017-07-03T15:06:36","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/?p=205"},"modified":"2017-07-30T23:33:09","modified_gmt":"2017-07-30T23:33:09","slug":"general-strategy-rules-thumb","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/general-strategy-rules-thumb","title":{"rendered":"General Strategy &#8211; Rules of Thumb"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>This section is more applicable for time trials where speed is paramount, and the levels are generally a bit less tricky, but these are good rules of thumb anyway. Unlike the &#8220;do not create 2 ends&#8221; rule, these are not always correct.<\/p>\n<h1>Work Outside -&gt; In<\/h1>\n<p>The general idea here is that when you have a big blob of tiles, the easiest way to avoid getting stuck is by doing circles around the edges first, then working towards the centre.<\/p>\n<p>A related idea is to keep things as round (or square) as possible, and have just one blob of tiles. This is an aesthetically pleasing and easy-to-follow\u00a0way to reduce the chance of creating extra ends, and otherwise identify problem areas where you may be forced to create an end.<\/p>\n<h1>Clear Red Tiles First<\/h1>\n<p>When I\u00a0see big blotches of red, I like to go only red first, unless it conflicts with the general idea above to work outside -&gt; in. The idea is that by removing red tiles, you simplify the situation, making it easier to see what you should do next.<\/p>\n<p>Be careful with this general idea, and try to keep it localized. Always prioritize the first rule of thumb, working from the outside in and keeping round\/square shapes. Personally, I like to combine the two, where I clear all the red tiles along the outside first, work outside -&gt; in, then clear the next set of outer red tiles, rinse and repeat.<\/p>\n<p>Below is an example putting these rules of thumb into work, on a random level:<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_194\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-194\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-194 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155401-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155401-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155401-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155401-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155401.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-194\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Hypothetical starting position<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_195\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-195\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-195 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155426-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155426-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155426-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155426-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155426.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-195\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Red tiles first, and only on the outside first<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_196\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-196\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-196 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155449-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155449-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155449-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155449-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155449.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-196\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Clearing more red tiles and on the outside (L shape of yellow tiles and the 6 red tiles box cleared)<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_197\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-197\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-197 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155457-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155457-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155457-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155457-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155457.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-197\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Note: this move is a bit tricky. I had to move down (shown here) in order to avoid creating extra ends<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_198\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-198\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-198 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155513-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155513-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155513-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155513-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155513.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-198\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">More working around the outside &#8211; I make sure to clear the red tile at the bottom first, as it can be problematic later. At this point, I have kept things tidy and won&#8217;t really be liable to being tricked and getting stuck anymore<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_199\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-199\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-199 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155525-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155525-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155525-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155525-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155525.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-199\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Continuing on the outside and clearing red tiles&#8230;<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_200\" style=\"width: 586px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-200\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-200 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155537-576x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"576\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155537-576x1024.png 576w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155537-169x300.png 169w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155537-768x1365.png 768w, https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/Screenshot_20170701-155537.png 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-200\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">And in a relatively clean and simple way, we can finish the level!<\/p><\/div>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/strategy-and-hints\">Back to Strategy and Hints<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This section is more applicable for time trials where speed is paramount, and the levels are generally a bit less tricky, but these are good rules of thumb anyway. Unlike the &#8220;do not create 2 ends&#8221; rule, these are not &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/general-strategy-rules-thumb\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[5],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/205"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=205"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/silentzebra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/205\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{